OL,3,CDeath of the gearbox? Automatic
OL,4,Cdriving tests skyrocket
OL,6,FThe gearbox could become a thing of
OL,7,Fthe past as new drivers ditch manual
OL,8,Fcars for simpler-to-use automatics.
OL,10,FIn 2007-8, 70,429 driving tests were
OL,11,Ftaken in automatic cars, according to
OL,12,FDriver Vehicle and Licensing Agency
OL,13,F(DVSA) data.
OL,15,FThat figure soared to 324,064 tests in
OL,16,F2022-23, which is an increase of more
OL,17,Fthan 360% over the course of 15 years.
