OL,3,CDeath of the gearbox? Automatic
OL,4,Cdriving tests skyrocket
OL,6,FManual tests meanwhile have seen a
OL,7,Fdecline. Around 1.69 million tests
OL,8,Fwere taken in manual vehicles in 2007-
OL,9,F08, down to 1.36 million in 2022-23.
OL,11,FThe number of tests taken more widely
OL,12,Fhas seen a slight drop since 2007-08,
OL,13,Fdown from 1.76 million to 1.69 million
OL,14,Fin 2022-23, but the pass rate of those
OL,15,Ftaking tests is up from 44.2% to
OL,16,F48.8%, DVSA data showed.
